comments.body:
@jszczepkowski Is there a reason why autoscaler has reference to scale subresource instead of to RC or Deployment? Is scale subresource stored in a separate object in etcd than the rest of the RC or Deployment?

(And yeah, as @ramr alludes to, the same question I asked about Selector can be asked about Replicas, which is also already in the top-level object's Status.)

Regardless, you should document why this field exists, otherwise people will wonder.

diffHunk:
@@ -1,1 +97,101 @@
	// Selector is a label query over pods that should match the replicas count.
	Selector map[string]string
}

@@ -1,1 +143,147 @@	// to maintain by adjusting the desired number of pods.
	// Currently this can be either "cpu" or "memory".
	Target ResourceConsumption
}

@@ -1,1 +163,167 @@	// LastScaleTimestamp is the last time the HorizontalPodAutoscaler scaled the number of pods.
	// This is used by the autoscaler to controll how often the number of pods is changed.
	LastScaleTimestamp *util.Time
}
